Ron Kolm Papers

Contents

Series I: Correspondence

Scope and Content

This series consists of correspondence between Ron Kolm and a wide range of downtown artists and writers.

Arrangement

This series is arranged alphabetically by correspondent and chronologically within each folder.

Series II: Manuscripts

Scope and Contents

This series contains manuscripts sent to Ron Kolm as a friend or as an editor. Included are many manuscript drafts by downtown writers.

Arrangement

This series is arranged alphabetically by author.

This series contains posters Kolm collected from the downtown scene. Included are posters for the Sex Pistols as well as posters for many downtown books, such as Raw magazine, and a variety of signed prints by downtown artists.

Accretions 2015-2016

Scope and Contents

These accretions consist of materials collected by Ron Kolm documenting the Soho and East Village arts and literary scenes, primarily in the years 2014-2016. Materials include flyers for poetry readings and other literary events; gallery announcements; promotional materials for upcoming books; correspondence with artists and writers; manuscripts in various stages; audio recordings; video recordings; and publications, including zines, newspapers, magazines, and literary journals.

Arrangement

These accretions have not been arranged by an archivist. The materials are arranged in the order in which they were received from the donor.

Conditions Governing Access

Audiovisual and born-digital materials have not been preserved and may not be available to researchers.

Accretions 2018, 1978-20172015-2017

Extent

2 Linear Feet in 1 record carton, 1 manuscript box, and 1 oversize file folder
4 dvd-r disks
4 sound discs (cd)

Scope and Contents

This accretion contains materials collected by Ron Kolm, documenting the Soho and East Village arts and literary scene. Materials include ephemera for events, gallery announcements, correspondence, newspapers, and literary and cultural publications. This accretion also includes audio and video recordings of literary and poetry readings, John Farris Memorial Service, and commercial music albums.

Arrangement

These accretions have not been arranged by an archivist. The materials are arranged in the order in which they were received from the donor.

Processing Information

Loose material was grouped into acid-free folders, keeping its original order. Overesized material was separated and placed in appropriate sized folders.

Scope and Contents

This accretion contains materials collected by Ron Kolm, documenting the Soho and East Village arts and literary scene.
